

Git Configuration :

System level git config is not needed to config, Change the config for Global, user level or repo level git config.

1 System level Config
2 User/Global level Config
3 Repo level Config

Global Config:

Updaets the config on the ~/.gitconfig 

git config --global user.name "Arun Amaran"
git config --global user.email "arunkumar.amaran@macys.com"
git config --global core.editor notepad++
git config --global help.autocorrect 1
git config --global color.ui auto
git config --global core.autocrlf true 


to update the config on repo just update the config on the repo where you are located and ignore the --global flag.
git config on a repo will change the conif

git log -- to view the commit history
git log --oneline --graph 
     to view the commit log in oneline option with branching graphed.

git shortlog is for summary of commis

git shortlog -sne 

git show will show the commit message
git show HEAD
git show HEAD~1

git diff
	 
We can branch from any commit and get the state of the project from that point on

git remote
 show the remote url

git remote -view

git remote add origin <git repoo>

git branch

git tag

git pull

git push




